   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Portions from Footnotes</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>40 1 This was a repetition of the devil's temptation in the wilderness 4:6 .</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>42 1 If He had saved Himself, He could not save us.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>46 1 God forsook Christ on the cross because He took the place of sinners 1 Pet 3:18 He bore our sins 1 Pet 2:24; Isa 53:6 and was made sin for us 2 Cor 5:21 .</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>48 1 Offered to the Lord in a mocking way Luke 23:36 for quenching His thirst John 19:28-30 and note 30 1 .</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>50 1 This was His giving up of His spirit John 19:30 ; it indicates that the Lord voluntarily yielded up His life Mark 15:37; Luke 23:46 .</S>
